text.tspan: Only ring-0 can trigger via 'int N'
(page fault loading a page from disk).
Timer IRQ must still fire so
If handler is slow AND another
call I/O or sleep they need
Trap gate so timer IRQ fires
Process running in ring-3 or ring-0
Restores EIP, CS, EFLAGS from stack
IF bit from SAVED EFLAGS is restored

p.strong: IRQ0 Timer Handler Interrupt Gate (0x8E, DPL=0)

div.p: Byte: [7] [6] [5] [4] [3] [2] [1] [0] Hex: XX XX 0x8E 0x00 0x08 0x00 lo(handler) lo(handler) ^^^^ ^^^^ ^^^^ offset[31:16] type+attr selector offset[15:0]
Byte 5 = 0x8E = 1000_1110b ^ present ^^ DPL=0 (ring-0 only, hardware delivers) ^ S=0 (system descriptor) ^ D=1 (32-bit gate) ^^^ type=110 = INTERRUPT gate clears IF

p.strong: #PF Page Fault Handler Trap Gate (0x8F, DPL=0)

div.p: Byte: [7] [6] [5] [4] [3] [2] [1] [0] Hex: XX XX 0x8F 0x00 0x08 0x00 lo(handler) lo(handler) ^^^^ type+attr = 0x8F
Byte 5 = 0x8F = 1000_1111b ^ present ^^ DPL=0 (ring-0 only, CPU exceptions self-deliver) ^ S=0 ^ D=1 (32-bit) ^^^ type=111 = TRAP gate preserves IF
Byte: [7] [6] [5] [4] [3] [2] [1] [0] Hex: XX XX 0xEF 0x00 0x08 0x00 lo(handler) lo(handler) ^^^^ type+attr = 0xEF THE CRITICAL DIFFERENCE

Byte 5 = 0xEF = 1110_1111b ^ present ^^ DPL=3 user-mode CAN invoke via 'int 0x80' ^ S=0 without triggering #GP! ^ D=1 (32-bit) ^^^ type=111 = TRAP gate IF preserved (timer fires during blocking syscalls)
